1
00:00:11,033 --> 00:00:11,900
<i> Emma?</i>

2
00:00:12,033 --> 00:00:13,633
<i>Out of all the places you
could've gone,</i>

3
00:00:13,767 --> 00:00:15,267
<i>you really had to come through
here?</i>

4
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:17,633
<i>Sorry, you're blocking the way.</i>

5
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:18,567
<i> Damn, girl!</i>

6
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:19,367
<i> Let's go swim?</i>

7
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:20,033
<i> Yeah.</i>

8
00:00:20,167 --> 00:00:21,233
<i> Come one, let's swim?</i>

9
00:00:21,367 --> 00:00:22,100
<i> I'll teach you.</i>

10
00:00:22,233 --> 00:00:23,167
<i> No need.</i>

11
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:24,933
<i> I already know how to swim.</i>

12
00:00:25,067 --> 00:00:26,433
<i> Mommy Jade taught me.</i>

13
00:00:26,567 --> 00:00:31,267
<i>She taught me many things,
like how to be independent.</i>

14
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:33,933
<i>You left Mookie to
be with your lover.</i>

15
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:35,333
<i> I didn't leave her!</i>

16
00:00:35,467 --> 00:00:37,700
<i>You did everything you could
to drive me out of my family</i>

17
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:39,400
<i>so you could steal them from me!</i>

18
00:00:39,533 --> 00:00:40,467
<i> Let me go!</i>

19
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:41,533
<i> You, shameless!</i>

20
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:42,900
<i> Our daughter is safe now.</i>

21
00:00:43,033 --> 00:00:44,133
<i> And you saved her.</i>

22
00:00:44,267 --> 00:00:46,400
<i>Caloy showed me her
picture when we met.</i>

23
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:47,800
<i>What do you want me to do
to her?</i>

24
00:00:47,933 --> 00:00:49,567
<i>Do you want me to kidnap her
or scare her?</i>

25
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:52,033
<i>I don't care what
you'll do to her.</i>

26
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:55,800
<i>Just take her
out of this resort.</i>

27
00:00:55,933 --> 00:00:57,133
<i> Zayn!</i>

28
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:32,567
Zayn.

29
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:34,167
- Zayn, that's Mom.
- Aunt Emma?

30
00:01:34,300 --> 00:01:35,767
- Aunt Emma!
- That's Mom!

31
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:37,133
Zayn, hurry up!

32
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:52,533
Mookie!

33
00:01:52,667 --> 00:01:53,933
Mookie, run away from here!

34
00:01:54,067 --> 00:01:55,500
Ask for help!

35
00:01:55,633 --> 00:01:56,400
Mom!

36
00:01:56,533 --> 00:01:57,200
Mom!

37
00:01:57,333 --> 00:01:58,500
Aunt Emma!

38
00:01:58,633 --> 00:02:00,533
Mom!

39
00:02:00,667 --> 00:02:01,300
Zayn!

40
00:02:01,433 --> 00:02:03,133
- Mookie!
- Let's go, Zayn!

41
00:02:03,267 --> 00:02:04,433
I hear Mom's voice over there.

42
00:02:04,567 --> 00:02:05,567
No, it's dangerous out there.

43
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:08,800
The staff says it's dangerous
inside that area.

44
00:02:08,933 --> 00:02:11,200
But we can't abandon Mom.

45
00:02:11,333 --> 00:02:12,367
Come on, Zayn!

46
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:13,933
Mooks, it's already dark.

47
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:15,033
We might get lost.

48
00:02:15,167 --> 00:02:16,767
-We might not find our way back.
-Let's go, Zayn!

49
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:18,267
We'll ask for help outside.

50
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:18,900
Let's ask for help.

51
00:02:19,033 --> 00:02:20,000
Zayn!

52
00:02:22,367 --> 00:02:26,033
<i>Don't worry,
our daughter is safe now.</i>

53
00:02:26,167 --> 00:02:27,400
<i> And you saved her.</i>

54
00:02:27,533 --> 00:02:29,833
<i>I'm scared of what
can happen to Mookie.</i>

55
00:02:32,933 --> 00:02:34,200
Dad!

56
00:02:34,333 --> 00:02:36,433
Dad!

57
00:02:36,567 --> 00:02:37,500
- Dad.
- Mookie!

58
00:02:37,633 --> 00:02:39,433
- Dad!
- Mookie.

59
00:02:39,567 --> 00:02:42,733
Dad, something bad
happened to Mom.

60
00:02:42,867 --> 00:02:43,667
What?

61
00:03:06,033 --> 00:03:07,200
Here's your food.

62
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:14,300
My daughter Emma.

63
00:03:14,433 --> 00:03:15,533
She's in danger.

64
00:03:15,667 --> 00:03:18,600
Please help her.

65
00:03:18,733 --> 00:03:20,667
You're just hungry.

66
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,133
Eat first.

67
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:23,800
Please help Emma.

68
00:03:23,933 --> 00:03:24,500
Here.

69
00:03:24,633 --> 00:03:26,533
No. What did you do to Emma?

70
00:03:26,667 --> 00:03:28,833
- Eat first. You're just hungry.
- What did you and Olive do

71
00:03:28,967 --> 00:03:30,033
to Emma?

72
00:03:30,167 --> 00:03:32,000
What is it?

73
00:03:32,133 --> 00:03:34,333
I haven't said anything yet.

74
00:03:34,467 --> 00:03:36,400
How did you know?

75
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:39,933
Wait, is that what they call
a mother's instinct?

76
00:03:40,067 --> 00:03:42,333
What did you and Olive do
to Emma?

77
00:03:42,467 --> 00:03:44,067
And what do you mean by Olive?

78
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,433
Miss Olive is dead.

79
00:03:46,567 --> 00:03:47,867
Miss Jade is my new boss.

80
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,033
No!

81
00:03:49,167 --> 00:03:50,467
Olive is still alive.

82
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:52,300
You're working for Olive.

83
00:03:52,433 --> 00:03:55,000
Jade was the one who died.

84
00:03:55,167 --> 00:03:58,833
Olive is pretending to be Jade.

85
00:03:58,967 --> 00:04:00,467
Pretending?

86
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:04,633
Wait. Are you saying Miss Olive
is fooling me?

87
00:04:04,767 --> 00:04:08,000
Maybe that's the reason
she tied you up.

88
00:04:08,133 --> 00:04:09,800
Because you found the truth.

89
00:04:09,933 --> 00:04:11,767
Help me, please.

90
00:04:11,900 --> 00:04:15,500
I must tell everyone the evil
things Olive is doing.

91
00:04:15,633 --> 00:04:17,567
Please help me. Let me out.

92
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:18,833
I'm begging you.

93
00:04:18,967 --> 00:04:22,467
I don't care if I'm working
for Miss Olive or Miss Jade.

94
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,000
What matters is I make money.

95
00:04:24,467 --> 00:04:26,200
So stop crying.

96
00:04:28,133 --> 00:04:30,067
Please have mercy on me.

97
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:31,733
Have mercy on my daughter.

98
00:04:31,867 --> 00:04:33,833
What did you do to her?

99
00:04:33,967 --> 00:04:35,667
You're just hungry.

100
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:36,433
Just eat.

101
00:04:36,567 --> 00:04:37,933
Have mercy on me.

102
00:04:38,067 --> 00:04:39,200
- Have mercy on me.
- Just eat.

103
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:40,533
Here you go. Just eat.

104
00:04:40,667 --> 00:04:41,733
What did you guys do?

105
00:04:41,867 --> 00:04:46,367
- Just eat so that...
- What did you do to Emma?

106
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:47,700
You're so dramatic.

107
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:57,167
Let me go!

108
00:04:57,300 --> 00:04:58,633
What do you need from me?

109
00:04:58,767 --> 00:05:00,000
Money? I don't have that!

110
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:02,233
I don't need money from you.

111
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,533
I need you.

112
00:05:04,667 --> 00:05:06,200
I want you.

113
00:05:15,867 --> 00:05:17,233
Help!

114
00:05:17,367 --> 00:05:20,200
- Help!
- Come here.

115
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:22,367
Don't! Help!

116
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:24,300
Don't!

117
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:27,200
Help!

118
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:27,933
Don't!

119
00:05:28,067 --> 00:05:29,133
I want you!

120
00:05:32,433 --> 00:05:33,733
Let go of my wife!

121
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:46,233
Okay.

122
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:50,600
- Okay.
- Thank you.

123
00:05:54,133 --> 00:05:55,467
Ma'am.

124
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,333
- Yes?
- Sorry for bothering you.

125
00:05:57,467 --> 00:06:01,700
I can't contact my parents.

126
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:05,900
The reception is weak
inside the forest.

127
00:06:06,033 --> 00:06:07,533
Please save them.

128
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:10,633
I don't want them to get harmed.

129
00:06:10,767 --> 00:06:12,000
For a moment.

130
00:06:12,133 --> 00:06:13,067
Okay.

131
00:06:14,967 --> 00:06:17,067
Hello, Sergeant Edroso?

132
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:19,100
This is Fe.

133
00:06:19,233 --> 00:06:21,633
Something happened
at the resort.

134
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,467
We need help.

135
00:06:31,967 --> 00:06:33,100
Okay.

136
00:06:35,133 --> 00:06:36,667
Ma'am, what do we do?

137
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:42,800
I'm sorry,
but it's already dark.

138
00:06:42,967 --> 00:06:45,400
It's dangerous
to enter the woods.

139
00:06:45,533 --> 00:06:48,033
But the police are on
their way here, right?

140
00:06:48,167 --> 00:06:50,400
Will my parents get rescued?

141
00:06:50,533 --> 00:06:55,900
Dear, the police station
is a bit far from here.

142
00:06:56,033 --> 00:06:59,467
But they'll be here
in 30 minutes.

143
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:00,600
Okay?

144
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:15,800
Dan!

145
00:07:20,633 --> 00:07:22,400
Dan, that's enough!

146
00:07:22,533 --> 00:07:23,900
Let's go! Let's leave!

147
00:07:24,033 --> 00:07:25,367
Come on!

148
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:26,367
Let's go!

149
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,867
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

150
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:35,933
Let's go, Emma!

151
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:45,867
I don't think we're in
the right direction.

152
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:50,500
We've been walking,
but we can't find the road.

153
00:07:50,667 --> 00:07:54,600
Dan, what's taking you so long?

154
00:07:54,733 --> 00:07:55,633
No, nothing.

155
00:08:01,233 --> 00:08:02,567
Wait.

156
00:08:02,700 --> 00:08:04,100
- Ouch.
- Where are we going?

157
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:06,800
Over here.

158
00:08:06,933 --> 00:08:07,700
Come on.

159
00:08:12,733 --> 00:08:14,267
Where's Danilo?

160
00:08:15,867 --> 00:08:17,467
Any update, Ma'am?

161
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:19,333
Baby girl, what's happening?

162
00:08:19,467 --> 00:08:21,433
Someone kidnapped Mom.

163
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:24,033
- Who is it?
- I don't know.

164
00:08:24,167 --> 00:08:25,567
What about Danilo?

165
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:26,567
He's in the forest.

166
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:28,600
He followed Mom.

167
00:08:28,733 --> 00:08:29,967
What?

168
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:31,400
Emma and Danilo are together?

169
00:08:32,933 --> 00:08:33,900
Come out now!

170
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:38,000
I'll eventually find you, fools!

171
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,033
Are there any reports?

172
00:08:56,167 --> 00:08:57,333
Any updates?

173
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:06,567
Looks like he's gone.

174
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:10,100
Let's go.

175
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:20,500
Wait. Why did you slap me?

176
00:09:20,633 --> 00:09:21,700
What if this was a cliff?

177
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:23,733
What if we died?

178
00:09:23,867 --> 00:09:24,667
What will happen to Mookie?

179
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:25,933
She'll be left in Jade's care.

180
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:32,967
What if that man caught us?

181
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:34,700
We'll both be dead, too.

182
00:09:39,433 --> 00:09:40,467
Sorry.

183
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:41,867
Sorry, it didn't cross my mind.

184
00:09:45,333 --> 00:09:46,400
Are you okay?

185
00:09:48,367 --> 00:09:50,167
What's that?

186
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:51,600
You're wounded.

187
00:09:51,733 --> 00:09:53,667
Why didn't you tell me?

188
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,167
I don't want you to worry.

189
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:07,567
<i> It hurts, right?</i>

190
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:13,900
Sit down first.

191
00:10:16,033 --> 00:10:18,467
We need to stop the bleeding.

192
00:10:20,433 --> 00:10:21,167
Don't you have a belt?

193
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:22,167
I don't.

194
00:10:29,867 --> 00:10:31,267
Emma.

195
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,400
I'm feeling weak.

196
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:34,700
Danilo, hang in there.

197
00:10:34,867 --> 00:10:36,133
We need to get out of here.

198
00:10:36,267 --> 00:10:37,567
We need to find help.

199
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:38,833
Okay?

200
00:10:42,233 --> 00:10:44,567
You can do it, okay?

201
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:45,667
We'll get out of here.

202
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,233
- Let's go.
- I'm feeling weak.

203
00:10:47,367 --> 00:10:48,100
You can do it.

204
00:10:48,233 --> 00:10:50,200
You can do it.
We'll ask for help.

205
00:10:57,900 --> 00:10:58,833
Emma, run away.

206
00:10:58,967 --> 00:11:00,200
Get out of this forest.

207
00:11:00,333 --> 00:11:01,967
That man might catch you.

208
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:04,033
I can't leave you!

209
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:10,200
I'm feeling weak.

210
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:11,100
I can't walk any longer.

211
00:11:11,233 --> 00:11:12,433
- Don't.
- I can't do it anymore.

212
00:11:12,567 --> 00:11:13,167
Dan!

213
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:14,533
Don't! Wait.

214
00:11:14,667 --> 00:11:16,533
Wait. We'll ask for help.

215
00:11:16,767 --> 00:11:18,967
Hang in there.

216
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:19,533
There.

217
00:11:19,667 --> 00:11:21,000
There's a hut.

218
00:11:21,133 --> 00:11:21,800
Come on. Hurry up.

219
00:11:24,367 --> 00:11:26,133
I'll go with you, Sir.

220
00:11:26,267 --> 00:11:27,633
I'm going, too.

221
00:11:27,767 --> 00:11:28,400
You can't, Ma'am, Sir.

222
00:11:28,533 --> 00:11:29,800
It's dangerous.

223
00:11:29,933 --> 00:11:31,167
Don't worry.

224
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:33,600
We'll catch
Miss Emma's kidnapper.

225
00:11:37,667 --> 00:11:38,033
<i> No.</i>

226
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:40,300
<i> They can't arrest Baldo.</i>

227
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:42,200
<i>They might find out
that I hired him.</i>

228
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:46,000
Sir, I'll go with you.

229
00:11:46,133 --> 00:11:48,000
I can't stay here and wait.

230
00:11:48,133 --> 00:11:50,533
I want to see Danilo.

231
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:52,267
Okay, Ma'am, as long as
you stay close to us.

232
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:54,067
Yes, yes. I will. I will.

233
00:11:58,367 --> 00:11:59,300
Just a little bit more.

234
00:11:59,433 --> 00:12:00,167
A few more steps.

235
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:08,133
Dan.

236
00:12:08,267 --> 00:12:09,000
Stay awake.

237
00:12:09,133 --> 00:12:11,267
I'll just ask for help, okay?

238
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:12,500
I'll ask for help.

239
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,933
Help!

240
00:12:16,067 --> 00:12:17,533
Anybody home?

241
00:12:17,667 --> 00:12:19,867
Hello? Please help us!

242
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:22,167
Hello?

243
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:24,433
Mookie, are you okay?

244
00:12:24,567 --> 00:12:25,600
Don't worry.

245
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:33,900
Flor, all Mom wants
is for us to talk.

246
00:12:35,767 --> 00:12:37,433
But I didn't let her.

247
00:12:37,567 --> 00:12:40,633
What if Dad wasn't
able to save her?

248
00:12:40,767 --> 00:12:42,500
What if something
bad happened to her?

249
00:12:42,633 --> 00:12:44,567
What if we can't talk anymore?

250
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:46,000
Please don't say that.

251
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:59,100
Don't think that way, okay?

252
00:12:59,967 --> 00:13:01,600
Nothing bad will
happen to Aunt Emma.

253
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:15,600
Aren't we leaving yet?

254
00:13:15,733 --> 00:13:17,133
- We're leaving now.
- Let's go!

255
00:13:33,233 --> 00:13:34,833
Help!

256
00:13:34,967 --> 00:13:36,933
Please help...

257
00:13:37,067 --> 00:13:41,100
What are you doing in
the forest at this hour?

258
00:13:41,233 --> 00:13:42,133
Please help us.

259
00:13:42,267 --> 00:13:43,567
My husband was stabbed.

260
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:44,700
What?

261
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:45,600
Wait.

262
00:13:45,733 --> 00:13:47,200
Bino, wake up.

263
00:13:47,333 --> 00:13:48,700
Hurry!

264
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:50,967
Someone needs help.

265
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:52,767
Hurry up.

266
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:53,700
Wait a minute!

267
00:13:55,733 --> 00:13:57,333
Hold on.

268
00:13:57,467 --> 00:13:59,367
Hurry up.

269
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:00,767
Hurry. Give that to me.

270
00:14:00,900 --> 00:14:01,933
Help them.

271
00:14:02,067 --> 00:14:03,767
Hurry!

272
00:14:03,900 --> 00:14:05,333
- Wait a minute!
- Please help us.

273
00:14:05,467 --> 00:14:06,300
- I'll help him.
- Come inside.

274
00:14:07,867 --> 00:14:08,633
Go on.

275
00:14:11,667 --> 00:14:13,500
Careful.

276
00:14:13,633 --> 00:14:15,667
Goodness! He's wounded.

277
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:17,533
Let's bring him into the room.

278
00:14:20,033 --> 00:14:21,633
Here, in the room.

279
00:14:21,767 --> 00:14:23,767
Come here.

280
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:24,633
Come in.

281
00:14:29,133 --> 00:14:30,433
Lay him down.

282
00:14:30,567 --> 00:14:31,333
He's wounded.

283
00:14:35,067 --> 00:14:36,167
Careful.

284
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:37,733
Thank you.

285
00:14:37,867 --> 00:14:39,100
Dear, wait for a minute.

286
00:14:39,233 --> 00:14:41,200
I'll just get a
herbal medicine.

287
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:42,767
I'll be right back.

288
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:46,300
And I'll get warm water
and a towel so we can wipe him.

289
00:14:46,433 --> 00:14:47,533
Okay.

290
00:14:47,667 --> 00:14:48,767
Dan, Dan.

291
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:54,900
Dan.

292
00:14:55,033 --> 00:14:56,567
Dan, don't sleep.

293
00:14:56,700 --> 00:14:59,400
Stay awake. Okay?

294
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:02,867
They'll treat you.

295
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:12,667
Dear, here are some clothes
so you can change.

296
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:14,933
It's already well-worn.
I hope it's okay with you.

297
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:16,400
I'll put this away.

298
00:15:16,533 --> 00:15:17,700
Thank you.

299
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:24,567
I'll leave you for now.

300
00:15:26,333 --> 00:15:28,167
Dan, I'll change my
clothes real quick.

301
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:29,000
Emma.

302
00:15:29,133 --> 00:15:30,733
Emma, wait.

303
00:15:30,867 --> 00:15:33,733
Don't leave me.

304
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:35,400
Don't leave me.

305
00:15:35,567 --> 00:15:36,833
Stay here.

306
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:04,200
Dan.

307
00:16:04,333 --> 00:16:06,700
Dan, I'm right here.

308
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:10,600
I never once thought of
leaving you or Mookie.

309
00:16:12,133 --> 00:16:13,467
I won't go anywhere.

310
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:23,900
Wait, I'll get you some clothes.

311
00:16:24,033 --> 00:16:25,200
Maybe that's why
you're shivering.

312
00:16:25,333 --> 00:16:27,000
Wait.

313
00:16:27,133 --> 00:16:31,233
Emma, stay here.

314
00:16:31,367 --> 00:16:33,133
Wait, I'll tuck you in.

315
00:17:09,233 --> 00:17:11,300
This forest is too dense.

316
00:17:11,433 --> 00:17:14,967
Many wild animals
come out at nighttime.

317
00:17:15,133 --> 00:17:16,800
Be careful.

318
00:17:16,933 --> 00:17:19,567
Sarge, when we catch him,

319
00:17:19,700 --> 00:17:21,633
can you let me punch Emma's
kidnapper

320
00:17:21,767 --> 00:17:23,133
I'll beat him up.

321
00:17:23,267 --> 00:17:25,467
- Okay, let's go.
- Let's go.

322
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:26,633
You promised.

323
00:17:32,167 --> 00:17:32,867
Are you okay?

324
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:33,733
Yes.

325
00:17:33,867 --> 00:17:34,767
- There!
- Where? Where?

326
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:36,400
Over there. Go check it out.
Hurry up.

327
00:17:36,533 --> 00:17:38,033
There, hurry up!

328
00:17:38,167 --> 00:17:39,400
Here?

329
00:17:39,533 --> 00:17:40,333
Take a look carefully
over there.

330
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,200
Madam.

331
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:46,067
It's me, Baldo.

332
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:48,000
Did you see anything?

333
00:17:48,167 --> 00:17:49,067
False alarm.

334
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:50,900
Maybe it's just a snake.

335
00:17:51,033 --> 00:17:53,467
- You startled me.
- Don't make a noise.

336
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,433
Where are Emma and Danilo?

337
00:17:55,567 --> 00:17:56,267
I don't know.

338
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:58,267
They escaped.

339
00:17:58,400 --> 00:17:59,933
Darn it.

340
00:18:00,067 --> 00:18:02,867
Get out of here before
they catch you!

341
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:04,133
Hurry up!

342
00:18:04,267 --> 00:18:04,833
Goodness!

343
00:18:07,467 --> 00:18:08,667
Wait, where's Jade?

344
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:10,333
- Jade?
- I'm here! I'm here!

345
00:18:10,467 --> 00:18:11,933
Jade!

346
00:18:12,067 --> 00:18:13,667
What are you doing there?

347
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:15,367
I'm hiding!

348
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:16,533
What do you think?

349
00:18:16,667 --> 00:18:18,567
Who knows what you
found over there?

350
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:20,767
Safety first, of course.

351
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:21,933
Let's go!

352
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:24,433
Let's find them.

353
00:18:24,567 --> 00:18:26,233
This way, Sir. Ma'am.

354
00:18:26,367 --> 00:18:27,167
We'll go straight?

355
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:28,167
Be careful.

356
00:18:56,433 --> 00:18:58,733
<i>Have you already forgotten
that we first met</i>

357
00:18:58,867 --> 00:19:00,267
<i> at a fishball stall?</i>

358
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:01,500
<i> Right?</i>

359
00:19:01,633 --> 00:19:05,167
<i>Every relationship goes
through challenges.</i>

360
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:09,267
<i>What matters is that
we're sticking together.</i>

361
00:19:18,067 --> 00:19:21,033
How do you feel?

362
00:19:21,167 --> 00:19:22,500
I'm feeling better now.

363
00:19:22,633 --> 00:19:24,233
Thank you.

364
00:19:24,367 --> 00:19:25,667
- Give that to me.
- Okay, give that to me.

365
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:26,667
Please bring this out.

366
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:27,800
Be careful.

367
00:19:29,567 --> 00:19:30,267
Have some coffee.

368
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:32,500
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

369
00:19:32,633 --> 00:19:34,067
Oh, Dear.

370
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:35,767
Don't be shy.

371
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:38,567
Bino and I do that, too.

372
00:19:38,700 --> 00:19:40,733
We cuddle while we sleep.

373
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:45,167
That's why our love
stays strong.

374
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:47,700
We're not a married couple.

375
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:49,000
What?

376
00:19:50,633 --> 00:19:54,833
Last night, you told me
that your husband needed help.

377
00:19:59,367 --> 00:20:03,167
We used to be a couple,
but we're now separated.

378
00:20:05,633 --> 00:20:09,567
That's hard to believe, Dear.

379
00:20:09,700 --> 00:20:11,700
Your eyes say differently.

380
00:20:13,667 --> 00:20:16,533
There's so much love in
the way you look at him.

381
00:20:16,667 --> 00:20:18,300
Just like me and Ebing.

382
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:24,600
I think you're only having
a misunderstanding.

383
00:20:24,733 --> 00:20:27,367
That's why you got separated.

384
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:30,300
You better talk things out.

385
00:20:30,433 --> 00:20:31,867
We'll leave you for now.

386
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:35,600
But come out in a few minutes
because the breakfast is ready.

387
00:20:35,767 --> 00:20:36,700
We will.

388
00:20:36,833 --> 00:20:37,433
Thank you.

389
00:20:37,567 --> 00:20:38,633
Don't forget the coffee.

390
00:20:38,767 --> 00:20:40,767
- Drink it while it's hot.
- Let's leave them.

391
00:20:43,567 --> 00:20:45,467
Is what Miss Ebing said true?

392
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:51,133
Did you call me your husband?

393
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:55,100
You also called me your wife

394
00:20:55,233 --> 00:20:57,367
when you were defending me
from the man last night.

395
00:20:57,500 --> 00:20:58,233
Right?

396
00:21:09,733 --> 00:21:10,833
What about Ador?

397
00:21:10,967 --> 00:21:12,333
What really happened to him?

398
00:21:12,467 --> 00:21:13,767
He's probably dead.

399
00:21:13,900 --> 00:21:15,633
I shot him, remember?

400
00:21:15,767 --> 00:21:19,133
<i>Ligaya, I know you're in there.</i>

401
00:21:19,267 --> 00:21:20,933
<i>I'll get you out of that place.</i>

402
00:21:21,067 --> 00:21:24,567
<i>I'll do everything,
even if it costs me my life.</i>

403
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:25,767
Where's Danilo?

404
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:27,467
Danilo!

405
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:29,200
There's only one bed.

406
00:21:29,333 --> 00:21:30,267
So, did you sleep there
together?

407
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:31,300
Darn you!

408
00:21:31,433 --> 00:21:32,600
You deserve that!

409
00:21:32,733 --> 00:21:33,567
Let go of her!

410
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:36,233
Why don't you ask that woman
what she did

411
00:21:36,367 --> 00:21:38,367
before you defend her?

412
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:41,033
What did she do to you
to hurt her again?

413
00:21:41,167 --> 00:21:43,000
Are you that stupid?

414
00:21:43,167 --> 00:21:49,133
This woman was so busy spreading
her legs for my fiancé!

415
00:21:49,267 --> 00:21:50,733
What?

416
00:21:50,867 --> 00:21:52,000
Ask her.

417
00:21:52,133 --> 00:21:53,400
Is what she said true?
